The paper deals with 3D image registration, which is a common problem in computer vision and medical imaging. The use of SURF keypoints and global optimization techniques suggests that the paper is likely to be in the computer vision (cs.CV) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of fast gradient descent algorithms, which are commonly used in optimization problems and could suggest the paper belongs to the information theory (cs.IT) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with large datasets and computational anatomy, which could suggest it belongs to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
